cast.overview: Jack Carter is a small-time hood working in London. When word reaches him of his brother's death, he travels to Newcastle to attend the funeral. Refusing to accept the police report of suicide, Carter seeks out his brother’s friends and acquaintances to learn who murdered his sibling and why.
cast.title: Get Carter

details.biography: Dorothy White was born on April 28, 1935 in Dumbarton, Scotland as Dorothy Margaret Cruikshanks Lowndes. She was an actress, known for Get Carter (1971), Coronation Street (1960) and New Scotland Yard (1972). She was married to David Dry and Hugh Dickson. She died on July 17, 1998 in Granada, Andalucía, Spain.
details.name: Dorothy White
